<font color="#FF0000">TO COOK</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 17 17:57:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
One more time. Many people demonstrated against the war in Vietnam because they objected to the loss of life not only of Americans - which ultimately totaled 58,000; but also of the 2 million Vietnamese who lost their lives.<br><br>
The arithmetic for 10 years of our involvement equates to 16,000 Vietnamese killed per month. <br><br>
This is the stark reality.<br><br>
As for me, I have no problem with people who were against the war which was typified, in my view, by the quote of a young Lieutenant in the Delta who said, &quot;We had to destroy the village, in order to save it.&quot;<br><br>
Call them sheep, cowards, traitors. Produce quotes which say the same. That is your right.<br><br>
Disagreeing with you is my right. <br><br>
Right?
<p><code>-- wingman@green.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


